# gen52 bilingual ratchet: the phatic register in Italian, same dialogue-act
# layer. Markers are closed-class conversational "function words" (not content).
# gen240: a lone "ciao" is a loanword (used in English too), so with a default
# (en) locale it greets in English; the clear Italian markers below switch to IT.
> ciao
< Hi there!
> grazie
< Prego!
> come stai?
< Sto bene, grazie. Come posso aiutarti?
> buongiorno
< Ciao!
